UDM Pro SE QEMU VM lab initramfs.

Changes from the vendor initramfs:
- CONFIGDEV points to /dev/disk/by-partlabel/config instead of /dev/mtdblock5.
- Foreign-kernel modules from the comparison initrd are available for QEMU virt.
- QEMU USB-storage modules are loaded early so the VM disk appears before the
  UDM mount scripts wait for GPT partition labels.
- If staged with prepare-mocks.sh, deterministic /mock hardware files and an
  ARM64 LD_PRELOAD shim are copied into the UDM root before systemd starts.
- The VM prepares missing QEMU lab netdevs for the UDM board profile, but it
  does not open WAN firewall ingress rules for the web UI.
- A QEMU-backed LAN member is kept attached to br0 so transparent QEMU
  networking can use the stock LAN web path on guest port 443.
- The UDM nginx setup-site template is installed when UniFi Core has not yet
  produced dynamic HTTP config in the lab VM.

The root filesystem, overlay setup, and final /sbin/init path remain the UDM
firmware boot path.
